    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>If your last name starts with &ldquo;B&rdquo; and ends with &ldquo;arnes,&rdquo; then some people at Duke think this fine university would suit you. No? If you&rsquo;re a 6-foot-8 forward from Ames, Iowa, perhaps you should consider matriculating to the school you visited this weekend. Not there yet? If you&rsquo;re Scout.com&rsquo;s No. 1 player in the country, you might look good wearing No. 40 for a place of higher education in Durham, N.C. Still no?</p>
<p>OK, one more try. How about: If you play basketball, go to college. That sounds right.</p>
<p>Also, if there&rsquo;s a Rolls Royce in your driveway, the NCAA kindly requests that you return it if you&rsquo;re not going to use it. That thing was probably expensive.</p>

